elf Portrait 2010 || ''Mackerel Go to a Tennis Court'' || Lim Cheol-bin\n|-\n| ''My Mom's Great Kimchi Stew'' || Han Seung-hun\n|-\n| rowspan=2|10 || rowspan=2|2011 || [[Im Kwon-taek]]'s Director's Special Award || ''The Driving Lesson'' || Choi Jai-young \n|-\n| Jung Il-sung's Special Award <br /> - Best Cinematography || ''Broken Night'' || Yang Hyo-joo\n|-\n| 12 || 2013 || [[Park Chan-wook]] Director's Special Award || ''When the Moon Is On the Wane'' || Jung So-young\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.msff.or.kr}}\n{{Festivals in South Korea}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mise-en-scene Short Film Festival}}\n[[Category:Awards established in 2002]]\n[[Category:Film festivals established in 2002]]\n[[Category:2002 establishments in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Annual events in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Film festivals in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Short film festivals]]\n[[Category:Summer events in South Korea]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Film Festival\n| name        = Mise-en-sc\u00e8ne Short Film Festival\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| number      = \n| location    = [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]\n| language    = International\n| founded        = 2002\n| date=June {{YEAR}}\n| website     = {{url|http://www.msff.or.kr}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Mise-en-sc\u00e8ne Short Film Festival (MSFF)''' is a Korean short film festival, intended to support upcoming young filmmakers. Since its launch in 2002, it is held every June in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ahn|first1=Sung-mi|title=Mise-en-scene Short Film Festival opens in Seoul|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140626000886|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=2015-10-28|date=26 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first1=Sora|last1=Ghim|title=The 14th Mise-en-sc\u00e8ne Short Film Festival Opens|url=http://bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=23100|website=BNTNews|accessdate=2015-10-28|date=25 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mise-en-sc\u00e8ne Short Film Festival (MSFF)|url=http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/coProduction/festivalView.jsp?seq=9|website=Korean Film Biz Zone|accessdate=2015-10-28|date=2015}}</ref>\n\n== Official Program Sections ==\nThe Mise-en-sc\u00e8ne Short Film Festival is organised into various sections:\n\n*'''Opening Film''': Moving Self-Portrait contains video clips shot by the entrants in the Competition in order to introduce themselves. \n*'''Competition''': The films are grouped into five genres.\n**A City of Sadness - Comments on Society\n**A Short Film About Love - Focus on Relationship\n**The King of Comedy - From Chaplin to Steven Chow\n**The Extreme Nightmare - World of Horror & Fantasy\n**The 40000 Blows - Action & Thriller on Mean Streets\n*'''Invitation Programs for Domestic Films'''\n*'''Awarded Films from last year'''\n\n== Awards ==\n\n=== Grand prize ===\n\n{|class=wikitable style=\"width:600px\"\n|-\n! width=10|No.\n! width=10|Year\n! Film\n! Director\n|-\n| 11 || 2012 || ''Forest'' || [[Um Tae-hwa]]\n|}\n\n=== Best Film in A City of Sadness ===\n\n{|class=wikitable style=\"width:600px\"\n|-\n! width=10|No.\n! width=10|Year\n! Film\n! Director\n|-\n| 1 || 2002 || ''Rotation'' || Noh Jin-sung \n|-\n| 2 || 2003 || ''The End of the Road'' || Park In-jae\n|-\n| 3 || 2004 || ''Feel Good Story'' || [[Lee Kyoung-mi]] \n|-\n| 4 || 2005 || ''Garivegas'' || Kim Sun-min \n|-\n| 5 || 2006 || ''Illegal Parking'' || Jeong Chung-hwan \n|-\n| 6 || 2007 || ''One Shiny Day'' || Yu Young-dae \n|-\n| 7 || 2008 || ''Enemy's Apple'' ||  [[Lee Su-jin (director)|Lee Su-jin]]\n|-\n| 8 || 2009 || ''[[Worst Friends (2009 film)|Worst Friends]]'' || Namkoong Sun \n|-\n| 9 || 2010 || ''Richard, the Elite University Student from London'' || Lee Yong-seung\n|-\n| 10 || 2011 || ''Social Service Agent'' || [[Kim Tae-yong (director, born 1987)|Kim Tae-yong]]\n|-\n| 11 || 2012 || ''Anesthesia'' || Kim Souk-young \n|-\n| 12 || 2013 || ''The Way Back'' || Kim Hal-la\n|-\n| 13 || 2014 || ''The First Grade'' || Lee Jung-